{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T17:54:20.819Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Convex vs non-convex"},{"type":"text","text":" describes the geometry of optimization problems and determines whether gradient descent can reliably find the best solution. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Convex functions"},{"type":"text","text":" have a single \"bowl-shaped\" minimum where any local minimum is guaranteed to be global, making them easy to optimize. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Non-convex functions"},{"type":"text","text":" (like neural networks) have multiple valleys, peaks, and saddle points, creating a complex landscape where gradient descent may get stuck in suboptimal solutions—this is why deep learning optimization is challenging and requires sophisticated techniques."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is — Clear definitions and intuition"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Convex function:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Definition"},{"type":"text","text":": A function is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"convex"},{"type":"text","text":" if the line segment between any two points on its graph lies "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"above or on the graph"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mathematical definition"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"f is convex if for any x₁, x₂:\nf(αx₁ + (1-α)x₂) ≤ αf(x₁) + (1-α)f(x₂) for all α ∈ [0, 1]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Shape"},{"type":"text","text":": Bowl shape curving upward (when minimizing)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Geometric intuition"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"      /\n     /   ← Convex function (bowl)\n    /\n   /______\n  \nDraw a line between any two points:\n  ------\nThe line is always ABOVE the curve\nNo bumps, no hidden valleys, no tricky spots [web:293]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Non-convex function:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Definition"},{"type":"text","text":": A function is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"non-convex"},{"type":"text","text":" if it does NOT meet the convexity criteria."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Shape"},{"type":"text","text":": Can have multiple dips, peaks, valleys, ridges"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Geometric intuition"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"  /\\    /\\\n /  \\  /  \\   ← Non-convex function\n/    \\/    \\\n\nDraw a line between two points:\n  ------\nThe line can dip BELOW the curve\nMultiple peaks, valleys, tricky spots [web:293]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key differences — Convex vs Non-convex"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Property"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Convex"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Non-convex"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Minimum types"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Single global minimum only"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multiple local minima + 1 global minimum"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Local vs global"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Any local minimum = global minimum"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Local minima ≠ global minimum (suboptimal)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Gradient descent"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Always converges to global minimum"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"May get stuck in local minimum"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Guarantees"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Strong guarantees (easy to solve)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Zero guarantees (hard to solve)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Complexity"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Relatively easy to minimize"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Relatively hard to minimize"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Saddle points"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"None"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common (flat regions with no gradient)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Examples"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Linear regression, logistic regression"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Neural networks, GANs, deep learning"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Convex optimization — Why it's easy"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key property:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Theorem"},{"type":"text","text":": If f is convex and differentiable, gradient descent converges to a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"global minimum"},{"type":"text","text":" (provided step size is small enough)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why?"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Convex function:\n  /\n /   ← Single bowl\n/______\n\nGradient always points downhill toward the bottom\nNo local minima to get stuck in\nGradient descent will always find the global minimum [web:290][web:291]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mathematical guarantee:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"For convex functions:\n- Any stationary point (∇f = 0) is a global minimum [web:288]\n- Gradient descent converges quickly to global minimum [web:288]\n- No local optima that aren't global [web:288]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Examples of convex problems:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Problem"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Loss function"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why convex"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Linear regression"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"MSE: (y - ŷ)²"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Bowl-shaped, single minimum"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Logistic regression"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Log loss"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Convex objective function"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Lasso/Ridge"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"L1/L2 + MSE"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sum of convex functions"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Non-convex optimization — Why it's hard"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key challenges:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Non-convex functions have"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Multiple local minima"},{"type":"text","text":" (where algorithm may get stuck)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Saddle points"},{"type":"text","text":" (flat regions with no gradient)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Complex surfaces"},{"type":"text","text":" with no simple path to best solution"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Visual example"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"  /\\    /\\\n /  \\  /  \\   ← Non-convex landscape\n/    \\/    \\\n   ↑\nGradient descent starting here:\n- May go down to left valley (local minimum)\n- May go down to right valley (global minimum)\n- Outcome depends on starting point! [web:287]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mathematical reality:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"For non-convex functions:\n- Many local optima that are NOT global [web:288]\n- Gradient descent arrives at local optimum (not guaranteed global) [web:294]\n- No guarantee of reaching global optimum [web:287]\n- Algorithms may converge to different solutions depending on starting point [web:287]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Neural networks are non-convex"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why deep learning is non-convex:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Neural network loss landscape:\n  Non-convex loss landscapes with multiple minima [web:289]\n  \nCharacteristics:\n- Multi-dimensional parameter space (thousands to billions of weights) [web:289]\n- Multiple dips and peaks (local minima) [web:290]\n- Complex surface with no simple path to best solution [web:290]\n- Saddle points and plateaus [web:295]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Real example"},{"type":"text","text":": Training GPT-4 optimizes on a non-convex loss landscape with billions of parameters."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"SGD as non-convex optimizer:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"SGD is a non-convex global optimization algorithm:\n- Relies only on gradient of objective function [web:289]\n- Noise helps escape local minima [web:289]\n- Explores smooth basins of attraction [web:289]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How gradient descent behaves"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"In convex problems:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Convex function:\n        /\n       /   ← Bowl\n      /\n     /______\n    ↑ start\n\nGradient:\n  ↓\n  ↓\n  ↓\n  ● (converges to global minimum)\n\nOutcome: Always reaches global minimum [web:291]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"In non-convex problems:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Non-convex function:\n  /\\    /\\\n /  \\  /  \\   ← Local min    Global min\n/    \\/    \\\n ↑ start\n |\n ↓\n ○ (converges to local minimum, STUCK!)\n\nOutcome: May get stuck in suboptimal local minimum [web:289][web:291]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why non-convexity is actually okay for deep learning"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key insight:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Don't fear non-convexity:\n- The high-dimensional landscape is often friendly [web:295]\n- Expect saddles and plateaus—they slow training but aren't dead ends [web:295]\n- In high dimensions, most local minima are close to global minimum [web:289]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why SGD works:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"SGD's noise helps:\n- Escapes shallow local minima [web:289]\n- Explores optimization landscape [web:289]\n- Finds smooth basins that generalize well [web:289]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Techniques for non-convex optimization"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Random initialization"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Start at different random points:\n→ Different initializations may lead to different minima\n→ Try multiple starts to find better solution [web:287]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"SGD benefits for non-convex:\n- Noise helps escape local minima [web:289]\n- Explores landscape more than batch GD [web:289]\n- Better at finding generalizable solutions [web:289]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Momentum"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"vₜ = γ × vₜ₋₁ + η × ∇J(θ)\nθ = θ - vₜ\n\nBenefit:\n- Smooths noisy updates\n- Accelerates in consistent direction\n- Helps navigate through saddles [web:268]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Learning rate schedules"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Start high (η = 0.1): Fast exploration, escape local minima\nDecrease (η → 0.001): Fine-tuning near minimum [web:266]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Adaptive methods (Adam)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Adaptive learning rates per parameter:\n- Automatically adjusts based on gradient history\n- Less sensitive to initial LR [web:268]\n- Often better for non-convex problems [web:268]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key takeaways"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Convex = bowl shape"},{"type":"text","text":": Line between any two points lies above graph"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Non-convex = multiple valleys"},{"type":"text","text":": Can have peaks, valleys, ridges"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Convex guarantee"},{"type":"text","text":": Any local minimum = global minimum"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Non-convex problem"},{"type":"text","text":": Local minima ≠ global minimum (suboptimal)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Convex GD"},{"type":"text","text":": Always converges to global minimum"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Non-convex GD"},{"type":"text","text":": May get stuck in local minimum"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Linear regression"},{"type":"text","text":": Convex (easy to optimize)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Neural networks"},{"type":"text","text":": Non-convex (hard to optimize)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"SGD"},{"type":"text","text":": Non-convex optimizer; noise helps escape local minima"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"High-dimensional reality"},{"type":"text","text":": Most local minima are close to global in deep learning"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For Generative AI, understanding convex vs non-convex is critical: neural networks, GANs, and transformers all optimize on non-convex loss landscapes with billions of parameters, making gradient descent uncertain and requiring sophisticated techniques like SGD, momentum, and adaptive methods to navigate the complex landscape successfully; this non-convexity is why deep learning optimization is challenging and why we need advanced optimization strategies beyond basic gradient descent."}]}]}}
